Clinical Diagnosis: BCC exc 
Location: Mid Lower Back
Method: Excision
Lesion Size: 0.5 x 0.8 cm
Excision Size, including margins: 3.6 x 2.4 cm
During Excision a 2nd lesion was adjacent to the site and was removed within this excision. 
The patient was evaluated preoperative and noted to be in stable condition. 
 Informed consent was obtained from the patient. All risks, benefits, and alternatives regarding the survey have been reviewed in detail with the patient. 
 This includes risks of bleeding, infection, scarring recurrence of lesion and need for further procedures. 
After consent was obtained, attention was turned toward the area of interest which was disinfected and cleaned with hibiclens. Local anesthetic, 2% lidocaine with epinephrine was infiltrated around the site. An elliptical incision with the appropriate margins was made using a Number 15 to obtain a full thickness specimen. Dissection of the surrounding/overlying tissue was performed to isolate, expose and remove the lesion. The specimen was placed in a bottle labeled A. #RA24-1109. 
Repair: Complex Closure 
The wound was closed with a complex closure on 05-20-2024. The wound size with margins is 3.6 - 2.4 cm. The defect was undermined extensively (2.4 cm) to reduce tension and distortion of the adjacent structures. Buried absorbable sutures were also used to close the subcutaneous and dermal components of the defect. The wound was approximated utilizing 3-O Vicryl and Using 3-O Nylon sutures. The final closure size is 4.2 cm. 
Pressure was applied to achieve hemostasis. Aquaphor was applied at the wound site and it was bandaged. Patient tolerated the procedure well and wound care instructions were reviewed and given to the patient.
