Clinical Diagnosis: LM (Raos request to send to pathology) 
Location: Left Jaw
Method: Shave
 The patient gave informed consent for this procedure. After consent was obtained, attention was turned toward the area of interest which was disinfected and cleaned with alcohol. Local anesthetic, 2% lidocaine with epinephrine was infiltrated around the area of interest. The superficial layers of the site were removed by Shave method using a Number 15. The specimen was placed in a bottle labeled A. #WC25-1846.
Pressure was applied to achieve hemostasis. Vaseline was applied at the wound site and it was bandaged. Patient tolerated the procedure well and wound care instructions were reviewed and given to the patient.
