Clinical Diagnosis: EXC r/o Digital Mucous Cyst
Location: Left 3rd Finger
Lesion Size: 0.2 x 0.3 cm
Excision Size, including margins: 0.7 x 1.6 cm
The patient was evaluated preoperative and noted to be in stable condition. 
 Informed consent was obtained from the patient. All risks, benefits, and alternatives regarding the survey have been reviewed in detail with the patient. 
 This includes risks of bleeding, infection, scarring recurrence of lesion and need for further procedures. 
After consent was obtained, attention was turned toward the area of interest which was disinfected and cleaned with hibiclens. Local anesthetic, 1% lidocaine with epinephrine was infiltrated around the site. An elliptical incision with the appropriate margins was made using a Number 15 to obtain a full thickness specimen. Dissection of the surrounding/overlying tissue was performed to isolate, expose and remove the lesion. The specimen was placed in a bottle labeled A. #RA25-2418. 
Repair: Simple Closure 
The wound was closed with a simple closure on 12-15-2025. The wound size with margins is 0.7 - 1.6 cm. The wound was approximated utilizing Using 4-O Nylon sutures. The final closure size is 2.5 cm. 
Pressure was applied to achieve hemostasis. Aquaphor was applied at the wound site and it was bandaged. Patient tolerated the procedure well and wound care instructions were reviewed and given to the patient.
